  "text": "Data for this study were collected from a survey of 180 full-time employees from over 20 different organizations located in Singapore. We recruited undergraduate students enrolled in business and social science classes to identify working adults from different industries and occupational status to participate in the study. Many studies have utilized this approach to collect data from a wide range of firms and industries (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and have shown that data collected with such procedures are of comparable quality with that of data collected through more traditional procedures (e.g., [CITATION_3] . A cover letter informed the participants that the aim of this research was to examine attitudes about work and family life, and that they were to return the completed questionnaires in sealed envelopes within three to five days. Participants were encouraged to respond as accurately and honestly as possible, and they were assured that their participation would be kept confidential, anonymous, and used strictly for academic research purposes only. Participants received a pen or a gift voucher as a token gesture of appreciation.",
